<figureCitation box="[913,982,962,989]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-62@5.[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Colastomion asperum Long, sp. n., female, holotype. 1 Habitus 2 Hypopygium (lateral view) 3 Mesonotum (dorsal view) 4 Head (lateral view) 5 Head (dorsal view) 6 Propodeum 7 Metasomal tergites 2–4 8 Fore wing 9 Hind wing." pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); distance between front and hind ocelli 0.7 × as long as OOL (2: 3) (
<figureCitation box="[485,554,998,1025]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-62@5.[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Colastomion asperum Long, sp. n., female, holotype. 1 Habitus 2 Hypopygium (lateral view) 3 Mesonotum (dorsal view) 4 Head (lateral view) 5 Head (dorsal view) 6 Propodeum 7 Metasomal tergites 2–4 8 Fore wing 9 Hind wing." pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); occipital carina complete but narrowly obliterated mediodorsally; face rugopunctate medially, with sparse striae laterally; frons flat, with sparse convergent striae laterally (
<figureCitation box="[1228,1296,1034,1061]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-62@5.[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Colastomion asperum Long, sp. n., female, holotype. 1 Habitus 2 Hypopygium (lateral view) 3 Mesonotum (dorsal view) 4 Head (lateral view) 5 Head (dorsal view) 6 Propodeum 7 Metasomal tergites 2–4 8 Fore wing 9 Hind wing." pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); vertex and temple coriaceous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,494,2033]" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis box="[199,327,1107,1132]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Mesosoma.</emphasis>
Length of mesosoma 1.5 × as long as high (72: 49); propleuron largely smooth, sparsely crenulate anteriorly; precoxal sulcus smooth; mesopleuron smooth; metapleuron rugo-punctate; notauli narrow and deep anteriorly, more or less flat posteriorly, with median carina between notauli (
<figureCitation box="[1000,1069,1178,1205]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-62@5.[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Colastomion asperum Long, sp. n., female, holotype. 1 Habitus 2 Hypopygium (lateral view) 3 Mesonotum (dorsal view) 4 Head (lateral view) 5 Head (dorsal view) 6 Propodeum 7 Metasomal tergites 2–4 8 Fore wing 9 Hind wing." pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); mesoscutum smooth; scutellar sulcus wide, 0.4 × as long as scutellum (5: 13) with one medial carina; scutellum smooth; propodeum with median depression crenulate, rugo-punctate laterally (
<figureCitation box="[664,733,1250,1277]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-62@5.[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Colastomion asperum Long, sp. n., female, holotype. 1 Habitus 2 Hypopygium (lateral view) 3 Mesonotum (dorsal view) 4 Head (lateral view) 5 Head (dorsal view) 6 Propodeum 7 Metasomal tergites 2–4 8 Fore wing 9 Hind wing." pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,494,2033]" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis box="[199,321,1287,1312]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Fore wing.</emphasis>
Pterostigma 5.0 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[507,523,1287,1313]" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">×</emphasis>
as long as wide (45: 9); vein r arising before middle of pterostigma; vein M+CU1 distinctly curved subapically (
<figureCitation box="[484,551,1322,1349]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-62@5.[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Colastomion asperum Long, sp. n., female, holotype. 1 Habitus 2 Hypopygium (lateral view) 3 Mesonotum (dorsal view) 4 Head (lateral view) 5 Head (dorsal view) 6 Propodeum 7 Metasomal tergites 2–4 8 Fore wing 9 Hind wing." pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); vein 1-SR+M slightly curved apically; vein cu-a postfurcal, reclivious; 2-CU1 6.7 × longer than 1-CU1 (40: 6); SR1: 3-SR: r = 56: 36: 11; vein 2-SR 5.0 × 2-SR+M (20: 4); 1-CU1: cu-a: 2- CU1: 3-CU1= 6: 7: 40: 9 vein r arising far before middle of pterostigma; second submarginal cell elongate, basal length 3.8 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[270,286,1431,1457]" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">×</emphasis>
as long as its apical width (42: 11) (
<figureCitation box="[699,768,1430,1457]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-62@5.[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Colastomion asperum Long, sp. n., female, holotype. 1 Habitus 2 Hypopygium (lateral view) 3 Mesonotum (dorsal view) 4 Head (lateral view) 5 Head (dorsal view) 6 Propodeum 7 Metasomal tergites 2–4 8 Fore wing 9 Hind wing." pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,494,2033]" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis box="[199,325,1466,1492]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Hind wing.</emphasis>
Vein M+CU 1.2 × as long as vein 1-M (29: 25); vein M+CU: 1-M: 1r-m = 29: 25: 15; vein 2- SC+ 
<collectionCode box="[201,220,1503,1529]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">R</collectionCode>
subquadrate (
<figureCitation box="[378,446,1502,1529]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-62@5.[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Colastomion asperum Long, sp. n., female, holotype. 1 Habitus 2 Hypopygium (lateral view) 3 Mesonotum (dorsal view) 4 Head (lateral view) 5 Head (dorsal view) 6 Propodeum 7 Metasomal tergites 2–4 8 Fore wing 9 Hind wing." pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,494,2033]" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1539,1564]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Legs.</emphasis>
Hind coxa smooth dorsally; length of hind femur: tibia: basitarsus: tarsus 1–5 = 49: 62: 38: 85; length of hind femur, tibia and basitarsus 6.1, 12.4 and 12.7 × as long as their width respectively; middle tibial spur curved and setose basally; apex of hind tibia with comb of specialized setae at inner side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,494,2033]" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis box="[199,323,1647,1672]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Metasoma.</emphasis>
First tergite 1.7 × as long as apical width (44: 26); first tergite with median carina on basal 0.6 of tergite; 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[250,266,1682,1696]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">nd</superScript>
metasomal tergite with developed midbasal triangular area giving rise to sinuate striae (
<figureCitation box="[1246,1314,1682,1709]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-62@5.[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Colastomion asperum Long, sp. n., female, holotype. 1 Habitus 2 Hypopygium (lateral view) 3 Mesonotum (dorsal view) 4 Head (lateral view) 5 Head (dorsal view) 6 Propodeum 7 Metasomal tergites 2–4 8 Fore wing 9 Hind wing." pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1350,1366,1682,1696]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">nd</superScript>
metasomal tergite 0.85 × shorter than medially long (30: 35), with indistinct midbasal triangular area giving rise to sinuate midlongitudinal carina, with irregular longitudinal striae; medial length of 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[999,1015,1754,1768]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">nd</superScript>
tergite 1.2 × its basal width (35: 30); 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[165,181,1790,1804]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">nd</superScript>
tergite 1.4 × than 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[399,413,1790,1804]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">rd</superScript>
(35: 26); medial length of 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[734,748,1790,1804]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">rd</superScript>
metasomal tergite 0.7 × its basal width (
<figureCitation box="[1200,1268,1790,1817]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-62@5.[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Colastomion asperum Long, sp. n., female, holotype. 1 Habitus 2 Hypopygium (lateral view) 3 Mesonotum (dorsal view) 4 Head (lateral view) 5 Head (dorsal view) 6 Propodeum 7 Metasomal tergites 2–4 8 Fore wing 9 Hind wing." pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); fourth tergite rugo-striate basally, punctate extremely apically; fifth-sixth tergites sparsely punctate; ovipositor smooth apically, with three ventral teeth subapically distal to apex (
<figureCitation box="[716,786,1862,1889]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-62@5.[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Colastomion asperum Long, sp. n., female, holotype. 1 Habitus 2 Hypopygium (lateral view) 3 Mesonotum (dorsal view) 4 Head (lateral view) 5 Head (dorsal view) 6 Propodeum 7 Metasomal tergites 2–4 8 Fore wing 9 Hind wing." pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,494,2033]" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1898,1924]" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Coloration.</emphasis>
Body yellow entirely, except median and lateral lobes of mesoscutum brown; stemmaticum black (
<figureCitation box="[160,228,1934,1961]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-62@5.[159,1429,234,1928]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Colastomion asperum Long, sp. n., female, holotype. 1 Habitus 2 Hypopygium (lateral view) 3 Mesonotum (dorsal view) 4 Head (lateral view) 5 Head (dorsal view) 6 Propodeum 7 Metasomal tergites 2–4 8 Fore wing 9 Hind wing." pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,494,2033]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,150,213]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="220" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,1971,1997]" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Male.</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[281,386,1971,1997]" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Paratype</typeStatus>
): body length 
<quantity box="[541,628,1970,1997]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="219" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
, fore wing 
<quantity box="[751,838,1970,1997]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="219" unit="mm" value="5.4">5.4 mm</quantity>
, antenna with antennomeres; 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1181,1195,1970,1984]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">rd</superScript>
segment of maxillary palp 1.6 × longer than maximally wide (13: 8); 5 
<superScript attach="left" box="[710,723,2006,2020]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">th</superScript>
segment as long as 6 
<superScript attach="left" box="[964,977,2006,2020]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="219">th</superScript>
segment (
<figureCitation box="[1090,1172,2006,2033]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1229,1253]" captionTargetBox="[179,1409,179,1203]" captionTargetId="figure-33@6.[179,1409,179,1203]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10–12. Colastomion asperum Long, sp. n., male, paratype. 10 Second-fourth metasomal tergites 11 Maxillary palp 12 Hind wing." pageId="4" pageNumber="219">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
); width of face: height of eye = 1.9: 2.5; fore wing vein 2-SR 5.3 × 2-SR+M (16: 3); second submarginal cell of fore wing elongate, basal length 3.8 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[270,286,187,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">×</emphasis>
as long as its apical width (42: 11); vein 2-SC+ 
<collectionCode box="[826,846,187,213]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="5" pageNumber="220">R</collectionCode>
of hind wing subquadrate (
<figureCitation box="[1154,1237,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1229,1253]" captionTargetBox="[179,1409,179,1203]" captionTargetId="figure-33@6.[179,1409,179,1203]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10–12. Colastomion asperum Long, sp. n., male, paratype. 10 Second-fourth metasomal tergites 11 Maxillary palp 12 Hind wing." pageId="5" pageNumber="220">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
